President Donald J. Trump has announced the formation of the President's Coronavirus Task Force, which will lead the United States Government's response to the novel 2019 coronavirus. The task force is led by Secretary of Health and Human Services Alex Azar and includes subject matter experts from various government agencies. Their goal is to monitor, contain, and mitigate the spread of the virus while providing accurate health and travel information to the American people. The risk of infection for Americans remains low, and the task force will work to prevent the spread of the new coronavirus. The task force members include Secretary Alex Azar, Robert O'Brien, Dr. Robert Redfield, Dr. Anthony Fauci, and other government officials.